title: Council on Human Reproductive Technology chairperson re-appointed
content_text:
p>
The Government today (April 11) announced the re-appointment of Dr Leong Che-hung 
as chairperson of the Council on Human Reproductive Technology, as well as the 
appointment and re-appointment of 21 members to the Council. Made by the Chief Executive, the appointments took effect today for a term of 
two years until April 10, 2009. Established in 2001 under the Human Reproductive Technology Ordinance, the 
Council on Human Reproductive Technology was tasked to regulate the conduct of

Council on Human Reproductive Technology was tasked to regulate the conduct of reproductive technology including embryo research in Hong Kong through a licensing system and the publication of a Code of Practice for the relevant professions. It consists of 26 members from a wide variety of disciplines, including medical specialists, legal professionals, social worker, scholar in philosophy and ethics, psychologist, sociologist, local community leaders and government representatives. The new membership list of the Council on Human Reproductive Technology is as follows: Chairperson
